<div class="content_max_width">
<h2 class="notopmargin">Tools and Technology</h2>
This site is a Content Management System (CMS) driven Website. It was produced based on Concordia University's Web template using Joomla! v. 1.5. Most tools and technologies used to produce the site are open source. We have used HTML and Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) to control the site layout and characteristics, PHP to run the application, MySQL and FileMaker Pro to store the data, and PhotoShop to manipulate graphics.<br />
<h2>Content</h2>
The content of this Website was collected, written, and edited by the John Molson School of Business (JMSB) External Affairs office under the direction of the JMSB stakeholders.<br />
<h2>Design</h2>
This site was developed, designed, and constructed by the Centre for Instructional Technology's (CIT) Web Team. The templates used were inspired by the University Communications Services' (UCS) Web team.<br />
<h2>Multi-Media</h2>
The videos that are included on this site were edited by CIT using videos originally produced by Concordia's Creative Media Services. Photographs and other images and logos are obtained from various internal and external sources.</div></div>

